quran[175]{c,v,t}:
  39,32,"And who is more unjust than he who lies against God, and calls the truth a lie when it comes to him? Is there not in hell a resort for those who misbelieve"
  39,33,"but whoso brings the truth and believes in it, these are they who fear"
  39,34,"For them is what they please with their Lord, that is the reward of those who do well"
  39,35,"that God may cover for them their offences which they have done, and may reward them with their hire for the best of that which they have done"
  39,36,Is not God sufficient for His servants? and yet they would frighten thee with those beside Him
  39,37,"But he whom God leads astray there is no guide for him; and he whom God guides there is none to lead him astray: is not God mighty, the Lord of vengeance"
  39,38,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely say, 'God!' Say, 'Have ye considered what ye call on beside God? If God wished me harm, could they remove His harm? or did He wish me mercy, could they withhold His mercy?' Say, 'God is enough for me, and on Him rely those who rely"
  39,39,"Say, 'O my people! act according to your power; I too am going to act; and ye shall know"
  39,40,"He to whom the torment comes it shall disgrace him, and there shall alight upon him lasting torment"
  39,41,"Verily, we have sent down to thee the Book for men in truth; and whosoever is guided it is for his own soul: but whoso goes astray it is against them, and thou art not a guardian for them"
  39,42,"God takes to Himself souls at the time of their death; and those which do not die (He takes) in their sleep; and He holds back those on whom He has decreed death, and sends others back till their appointed time;- verily, in that are signs unto a people who reflect"
  39,43,"Do they take besides God intercessors? Say, 'What! though they have no control over anything and have no sense"
  39,44,"Say, 'God's is the intercession, all of it; His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; then unto Him shall ye be sent back"
  39,45,"And when God alone is mentioned the hearts of those who believe not in the hereafter quake, and when those beside Him are mentioned, lo, they are joyful"
  39,46,"Say, 'O God! originator of the heavens and the earth, who knowest the unseen and the visible, thou wilt judge between thy servants concerning that whereon they do dispute"
  39,47,"And had those who do wrong all that is in the earth, and the like thereof with it, they would ransom themselves therewith from the evil of the torment on the resurrection day! but there shall appear to them from God that which they had not reckoned on"
  39,48,and the evils of what they have earned shall appear to them; but that shall close in on them at which they mocked
  39,49,"And when harm touches man he calls on us; then, when we grant him favour from us, he says, 'Verily, I am given it through knowledge!' nay, it is a trial,- but most of them do not know"
  39,50,"Those before them said it too, but that availed them not which they had earned"
  39,51,"and there befell them the evil deeds of what they had earned: and those who do wrong of these (Meccans), there shall befall them too the evil deeds of what they had earned, nor shall they frustrate Him"
  39,52,"Have they not known that God extends His provision to whom He pleases, or doles it out? verily, in that are signs unto a people who believe"
  39,53,"Say, 'O my servants! who have been extravagant against their own souls!' be not in despair of the mercy of God; verily, God forgives sins, all of them; verily, He is forgiving, merciful"
  39,54,"But turn repentant unto your Lord, and resign yourselves to Him, before there comes on you torment! then ye shall not be helped"
  39,55,"and follow the best of what has been sent down to you from your Lord, before there come on you the torment suddenly, ere ye can perceive"
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say, 'O my sighing! for what I have neglected towards God! for, verily, I was amongst those who did jest"
  39,57,"or lest it should say, 'If God had but guided me, I should surely have been of those who fear"
  39,58,"or lest it should say, when it sees the torment, 'Had I another turn I should be of those who do well"
  39,59,"Yea! there came to thee my signs and thou didst call them lies, and wert too big with pride, and wert of those who misbelieved"
  39,60,"And on the resurrection day thou shalt see those who lied against God, with their faces blackened. Is there not in hell a resort for those who are too big with pride"
  39,61,"And God shall rescue those who fear Him, into their safe place; no evil shall touch them, nor shall they be grieved"
  39,62,"God is the creator of everything, and He is guardian over everything"
  39,63,"His are the keys of the heavens and the earth; and those who misbelieve in the signs of God, they it is who lose"
  39,64,"Say, 'What! other than God would you bid me serve, O ye ignorant ones"
  39,65,"When He has inspired thee and those before thee that, \"If thou dost associate aught with Him, thy work will surely be in vain, and thou shalt surely be of those who lose"
  39,66,"Nay, but God do thou serve, and be of those who do give thanks"
  39,67,"And they do not value God at His true value; while the earth all of it is but a handful for Him on the resurrection day, and the heavens shall be rolled up in His right hand! Celebrated be His praise! and exalted be He above what they associate with Him"
  39,68,"And the trumpet shall be blown, and those who are in the heavens and in the earth shall swoon, save whom God pleases. Then it shall be blown again, and, lo! they shall stand up and look on"
  39,69,"And the earth shall beam with the light of its Lord, and the Book shall be set forth, and the prophets and martyrs shall be brought; and it shall be decreed between them in truth, and they shall not be wronged"
  39,70,"And every soul shall be paid for what it has done, and He knows best that which they do"
  39,71,"and those who misbelieve shall be driven to hell in troops; and when they come there, its doors shall be opened, and its keepers shall say to them, 'Did not apostles from amongst yourselves come to you to recite to you the signs of your Lord, and to warn you of the meeting of this day of yours?' They shall say, 'Yea, but the sentence of torment was due against the misbelievers"
  39,72,"It shall be said, 'Enter ye the gates of hell, to dwell therein for aye! Hell is the resort of those who are too big with pride"
  39,73,"But those who fear their Lord shall be driven to Paradise in troops; until they come there, its doors shall be opened, and its keepers shall say to them, 'Peace be upon you, ye have done well! so enter in to dwell for aye"
  39,74,"and they shall say, ' Praise be to God, who hath made good His promise to us, and hath given us the earth to inherit! We establish ourselves in Paradise wherever we please; and goodly is the reward of those who work"
  39,75,"And thou shalt see the angels circling round about the throne, celebrating the praise of their Lord; and it shall be decided between them in truth; and it shall be said, 'Praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,1,M
  40,2,"The sending down of the Book from God, the mighty, the knowing"
  40,3,"the forgiver of sin and accepter of repentance, keen at punishment, longsuffering! there is no god but He! to whom the journey is"
  40,4,None wrangle concerning the signs of God but those who misbelieve; then let not their going to and fro in the cities deceive thee
  40,5,"The people of Noah before them called the prophets liars; and the confederates after them; and every nation schemed against their Apostle to catch him. And they wrangled with falsehood that they might refute the truth thereby, but I seized them, and how was my punishment"
  40,6,"Thus was the sentence of thy Lord due against those who misbelieved, that they are the fellows of the Fire"
  40,7,"Those who bear the throne and those around it celebrate the praise of their Lord, and believe in Him, and ask pardon for those who believe: 'Our Lord! thou dost embrace all things in mercy and knowledge, then pardon those who turn repentant and follow thy way, and guard them from the torment of hell"
  40,8,"Our Lord! make them enter into gardens of Eden which thou hast promised to them, and to those who do well of their fathers, and their wives, and their seed; verily, thou art the mighty, the wise"
  40,9,"and guard them from evil deeds, for he whom thou shalt guard from evil deeds on that day, thou wilt have had mercy on, and that is mighty bliss"
  40,10,"Verily, those who misbelieve shall be cried out to, 'Surely, God's hatred is greater than your hatred of each other when ye were called unto the faith and misbelieved"
  40,11,"They shall say, 'Our Lord! Thou hast killed us twice, and Thou hast quickened us twice; and we do confess our sins: is there then a way for getting out"
  40,12,"That is because when God alone was proclaimed ye did disbelieve; but when partners were joined to Him ye did believe; but judgment belongs to God, the high, the great"
  40,13,"He it is who shows you His signs, and sends down to you from heaven provision; but none is mindful except him who turns repentant"
  40,14,"then call on God, being sincere in your religion to Him, averse although the misbelievers be"
  40,15,"Exalted of degrees! The Lord of the throne! He throws the spirit by His bidding upon whom He will of His servants, to give warning of the day of meeting"
  40,16,"The day when they shall be issuing forth, naught concerning them shall be hidden from God. Whose is the kingdom on that day?- God's, the one, the dominant"
  40,17,"today shall every soul be recompensed for that which it has earned. There is no wrong today; verily, God is quick at reckoning up"
  40,18,"And warn them of the day that approaches, when hearts are choking in the gullets; those who do wrong shall have no warm friend, and no intercessor who shall be obeyed"
  40,19,He knows the deceitful of eye and what men's breasts conceal
  40,20,"and God decides with truth; but those they call on beside Him do not decide at all: verily, God, He both hears and looks"
  40,21,"Have, they not journeyed on in the earth and seen how was the end of those who journeyed on before them? They were stronger than them in might, and their vestiges are in the land, but God caught them up in their sins, and they had none to guard them against God"
  40,22,"That is for that their apostles did come to them with manifest signs, and they misbelieved, and God caught them up; verily, He is mighty, keen to punish"
  40,23,"And we did send Moses with our signs, and with obvious authority"
  40,24,"unto Pharaoh and Haman and Qarun. They said, 'A lying sorcerer"
  40,25,"and when they came to them with truth from us, they said, 'Kill the sons of those who believe with him, and let their women live!' but the stratagem of the misbelievers is only in error"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, 'Let me kill Moses; and then let him call upon his Lord! verily, I fear that he will change your religion, or that he will cause evil doing to appear in the land"
  40,27,"And Moses said, 'Verily, I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every one who is big with pride and believes not on the day of reckoning"
  40,28,"And a believing man of Pharaoh's people, who concealed his faith, said, 'Will ye kill a man for saying, My Lord is God, when he has come to you with manifest signs from your Lord? and if he be a liar, against him is his lie; and if he be truthful, there will befall you somewhat of that which he threatens you; verily, God guides not him who is an extravagant liar"
  40,29,"O my people! yours is the kingdom today, ye are eminent in the land, but who will help us against the violence of God, if it comes upon us?' Said Pharaoh, 'I will only show you what I see, and I will only guide you into the way of right direction"
  40,30,"And he who believed said, 'O my people! verily, I fear for you the like of the day of the confederates"
  40,31,"the like of the wont of the people of Noah and 'Ad and Haman, and of those after them; for God desires not injustice for His servants"
  40,32,"O my people! verily, I fear for you the day of crying out"
  40,33,"the day when ye shall turn your backs, fleeing, with no defender for you against God; for he whom God leads astray, for him there is no guide"
  40,34,"And Joseph came to you before with manifest signs, but ye ceased not to doubt concerning what he brought you, until, when he perished, ye said, \"God will not send after him an apostle;\" thus does God lead astray him who is extravagant, a doubter"
  40,35,Those who wrangle concerning the signs of God without authority having come to them are greatly hated by God and by those who believe; thus does God set a stamp upon the heart of every tyrant too big with pride
  40,36,"And Pharaoh said, 'O Haman! build for me a tower, haply I may reach the tracts"
  40,37,"the tracts of heaven, and may mount up to the God of Moses, for, verily, I think him a liar.' And thus was his evil deed made seemly to Pharaoh, and he was turned from the way; but Pharaoh's stratagem ended only in ruin"
  40,38,"and he who believed said, 'O my people! follow me, I will guide you to the way of the right direction"
  40,39,"O my people! verily, the life of this world is but a provision, but, verily, the hereafter, that is the abode of stability"
  40,40,"Whoso does evil, he shall only be recompensed with the like thereof , and whoso does right, be it male or female and a believer, these shall enter into Paradise; they shall be provided therein without count"
  40,41,"O my people! why should I call you to salvation, and you call me to the fire"
  40,42,"Ye call on me to disbelieve in God, and to join with Him what I have no knowledge of; but I call you to the mighty forgiving One"
  40,43,"no doubt that what ye call me to, ought not to be called on in this world or in the hereafter, and that we shall be sent back to God, and that the extravagant, they are the fellows of the Fire"
  40,44,"But ye shall remember what I say to you; and I entrust my affair to God, verily, God looks upon His servants"
  40,45,"And God guarded him from the evils of what they plotted, and there closed in upon Pharaoh evil woe"
  40,46,"The fire - they shall be exposed to it morning and evening; and 'on the day the Hour shall arise,' enter, O people of Pharaoh! into the keenest torment"
  40,47,"And when they argue together in the fire, and the weak say to those who were big with pride, 'Verily, we were followers of yours, can ye then avail us against a portion of the fire"
  40,48,"Those who were big with pride shall say, 'Verily, we are all in it; verily, God has judged between His servants"
  40,49,"And those who are in the fire shall say unto the keepers of hell, 'Call upon your Lord to lighten from us one day of the torment"
  40,50,"They shall say, 'Did not your apostles come to you with manifest signs?' They shall say, 'Yea!' They shall say, 'Then call!- but the call of the misbelievers is only in error"
  40,51,"Verily, we will help our apostles, and those who believe, in the life of this world and on the day when the witnesses shall stand up"
  40,52,"the day when their excuse shall not avail the unjust; but for them is the curse, and for them is an evil abode"
  40,53,And we did give Moses the guidance; and we made the children of Israel to inherit the Book
  40,54,as a guidance and a reminder to those endowed with minds
  40,55,"Be thou patient, then; verily, God's promise is true: and ask thou forgiveness for thy sins, and celebrate the praise of thy Lord in the evening and in the morn"
  40,56,"Verily, those who wrangle concerning the signs of God without authority having come to them, there is naught in their breasts but pride; but they shall not attain it: do thou then seek refuge in God; verily, He both hears and looks"
  40,57,"Surely the creation of the heavens and the earth is greater than the creation of man: but most men know it not"
  40,58,"The blind and the seeing shall not be deemed alike, nor those who believe and do right and the evildoer; little is it that they remember"
  40,59,"Verily, the Hour will surely come; there is no doubt therein; but most men do not believe"
  40,60,"And your Lord said, 'Call upon me, I will answer you; verily, those who are too big with pride to worship shall enter into hell, shrinking up"
  40,61,"God it is who has made for you the night to repose therein, and the day to see by; verily, God is Lord of grace to men, but most men give no thanks"
  40,62,"There is God for you! your Lord the creator of everything! there is no god but He, how then can ye lie"
  40,63,Thus did those lie who gainsaid the signs of God
  40,64,"God it is who has made for you the earth as a resting-place, and a heaven as building, and has formed you and made excellent your forms; and has provided you with good things! there is God for you!- your Lord! then blessed be God, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,65,"He is the living One, there is no god but He! then call on Him, being sincere in your religion to Him; praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,66,"Say, 'Verily, I am forbidden to serve those whom ye call on beside God, since there have come to me manifest signs from my Lord, and I am bidden to be resigned unto the Lord of the worlds"
  40,67,"He it is who created you from the earth, then from a clot, then from congealed blood, then He brings you forth a child; then ye reach to puberty; then do ye become old men,- though of you there are some who are taken away before,- that ye may reach an appointed time, and haply ye may have some sense"
  40,68,"He it is who quickens and kills, and when He decrees a matter, then He only says to it, 'BE,' and it is"
  40,69,Hast thou not seen those who wrangle concerning the signs of God how they are turned away
  40,70,"Those who call the Book, and what we have sent our apostles with, a lie, soon shall they know"
  40,71,"when the fetters are on their necks and the chains, as they are dragged"
  40,72,into hell!- then in the fire shall they be baked
  40,73,"Then it shall be said to them, 'Where is what ye did associate"
  40,74,"beside God?' They shall say, 'They have strayed away from us; nay, we did not call before upon anything!' - thus does God lead the misbelievers astray"
  40,75,There! for 'that ye did rejoice in the land without right; and for that ye did exult
  40,76,"enter ye the gates of hell, to dwell therein for aye; for evil is the resort of those who are too big with pride"
  40,77,"But be thou patient; verily, the promise of God is true; and whether we show thee a part of what we promised them, or whether we surely take thee to ourself, unto us shall they be returned"
  40,78,"And we did send apostles before thee: of them are some whose stories we have related to thee, and of them are some whose stories we have not related to thee; and no apostle might ever bring a sign except by the permission of God; but when God's bidding came it was decided with truth, and there were those lost who deemed it vain"
  40,79,"God it is who has made for you cattle, that ye may ride on some of them;- and of them ye eat"
  40,80,and ye have in them advantages;- and that ye may attain thereon a want which is in your breasts; upon them and upon ships are ye borne
  40,81,He shows you His signs; which sign then of your Lord do ye deny
  40,82,"Have they not journeyed on in the land and seen how was the end of those before them, who were more numerous than they and stronger in might, and in their vestiges which are still in the land? but of no avail to them was that which they had earned"
  40,83,And when there came to them their apostles with manifest signs they rejoiced in what knowledge they had; but there closed in upon them that whereat they had mocked
  40,84,"And when they saw our violence they said, 'We believe in God alone, and we disbelieve in what we once associated with Him"
  40,85,"But their faith was of no avail to them when they saw our violence - the course of God with His servants in time past, and there the misbelievers lose"
  41,1,M
  41,2,"A revelation from the merciful, the compassionate"
  41,3,a book whose signs are detailed; an Arabic Qur'an for a people who do know
  41,4,a herald of glad tidings and a warning. But most of them turn aside and do not hear
  41,5,"and say, 'Our hearts are veiled from what thou dost call us to, and in our ears is dullness, and between us and thee there is a veil. Act thou; verily, we are acting too"
  41,6,"Say, 'I am but a mortal like yourselves, I am inspired that your God is one God; then go straight to Him, and ask forgiveness of Him; and woe to the idolaters"
  41,7,"who give not alms, and in the hereafter disbelieve"
  41,8,"Verily, those who believe and do right, for them is a hire that is not grudged"
  41,9,"Say, 'What! do ye really misbelieve in Him who created the earth in two days, and do ye make peers for Him?- that is the Lord of the worlds"
  41,10,"And He placed thereon firm mountains above it and blessed it, and apportioned therein its foods in four days alike for those who ask"
  41,11,"Then He made for the heaven and it was but smoke, and He said to it and to the earth, 'Come, ye two, whether ye will or no!' They said, 'We come willingly"
  41,12,"And He decreed them seven heavens in two days, and inspired every heaven with its bidding: and we adorned the lower heaven with lamps and guardian angels; that is the decree of the mighty, the knowing One"
  41,13,"But if they turn aside, then say, 'I have warned you of a thunder-clap like the thunder-clap of 'Ad and Thamud"
  41,14,"when their apostles came to them from before them and from behind them (saying), \"Serve ye none but God.\"' They said, 'If our Lord pleased He would send down angels; so we in what ye are sent with disbelieve"
  41,15,"And as for 'Ad, they were big with pride in the land, without right, and said, 'Who is stronger than us in might?' Did they not see that God who created them He was stronger than they in might? But they did gainsay our signs"
  41,16,"And we sent upon them a cold blast in unfortunate days, that we might make them taste the torment of disgrace in the life of this world;- but the torment of the hereafter is more disgraceful, and they shall not be helped"
  41,17,"And as for Thamud we guided them; but they preferred blindness to guidance, and the thunder-clap of the torment of abasement caught them for what they had earned"
  41,18,but we saved those who believed and who did fear
  41,19,"And the day when the enemies of God shall be gathered together into the fire, marshalled along"
  41,20,"until when they come to it, their hearing and their eyesight and their skins shall bear witness against them of that which they have done"
  41,21,"And they shall say to their skins, 'Why have ye borne witness against us?' they shall say, 'God gave us speech who has given speech to everything; He created you at first, and unto Him shall ye be returned"
  41,22,"and ye could not conceal yourselves that your hearing and your eyesight should not be witness against you, nor your skins; but ye thought that God did not know much of what ye do"
  41,23,"And that thought of yours which ye thought concerning your Lord has destroyed you, and ye have now become of those who lose"
  41,24,"And if they are patient, still the fire is a resort for them; and if they ask for favour again, they shall not be taken into favour"
  41,25,"We will allot to them mates, for they have made seemly to them what was before them and what was behind them; and due against them was the sentence on the nations who passed away before them; both of ginns and of mankind; verily, they were the losers"
  41,26,"Those who misbelieve say, 'Listen not to this Qur'an, but talk foolishly about it, haply ye may gain the upper hand"
  41,27,But we will make those who misbelieve taste keen torment; and we will recompense them with the worst of that which they have done
  41,28,"That is, the recompense of the enemies of God,- the fire! for them is an eternal abode therein: a recompense for that they did gainsay our signs"
  41,29,"And those who misbelieved say, 'Our Lord, show us those who have led us astray amongst the ginns and mankind; we will place them beneath our feet, and they shall both be amongst those who are put down"
  41,30,"Verily, those who say, 'Our Lord is God,' and then go straight, the angels descend upon them - 'fear not and be not grieved, but receive the glad tidings of Paradise which ye were promised"
  41,31,"we are your patrons in the life of this world and in the next, and ye shall have therein what your souls desire, and ye shall have therein what ye call for"
  41,32,"an entertainment from the forgiving, the merciful"
  41,33,"And who speaks better than he who calls to God and does right, and says, 'Verily, I am of those resigned"
  41,34,"Good and evil shall not be deemed alike; repel (evil) with what is best, and lo! He between whom and thyself was enmity is as though he were a warm patron"
  41,35,But none shall meet with it save those who are patient; and none shall meet with it save those who are endowed with mighty good fortune
  41,36,"And if an incitement from the devil incites you, then seek refuge in God; verily, He both hears and knows"
  41,37,"And of His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. Adore ye not the sun, neither the moon; but adore God who created you, if it be Him ye serve"
  41,38,"But if they be too big with pride - yet those who are with thy Lord celebrate His praises by night and day, and they are never weary"
  41,39,"And of His signs (is this), that thou mayest see the earth drooping, and when we send down water upon it it stirs and swells; verily, He who quickens it will surely quicken the dead; verily, He is mighty over all"
  41,40,"Verily, those who are inclined to oppose our signs are not hidden from us. Is he who is cast into the fire better, or he who comes safe on the resurrection day? Do what ye will: verily, He on what ye do doth look"
  41,41,"Verily, those who misbelieve in the reminder when it comes to them - and, verily, it is a glorious Book"
  41,42,"falsehood shall not come to it, from before it, nor from behind it - a revelation from the wise, the praiseworthy One"
  41,43,"Naught is said to thee but what was said to the apostles before thee, 'Verily, thy Lord is Lord of forgiveness and Lord of grievous torment"
  41,44,"And had we made it a foreign Qur'an, they would have said, 'Unless its signs be detailed. .. . What! foreign and Arabic?' Say, 'It is, for those who believe, a guidance and a healing. But those who believe not, in their ears is dullness, and it is blindness to them; these are called to from a far-off place"
  41,45,"And we gave Moses the Book, and it was disputed about; but had it not been for thy Lord's word already passed it would have been decided between them, for, verily, they were in hesitating doubt thereon"
  41,46,"Whoso does right it is for his soul, and whoso does evil it is against it, for thy Lord is not unjust towards His servants"